  "aspect": "vertical", "theme": "navy", "fps": 30, "crossfade": 0.6,
  "voiceover": "Where is God when it hurts? This isn't an argument to win — it's a wound to sit with. Christianity's answer isn't a clever explanation. It's a God who didn't stay at a safe distance from pain. In Jesus, God entered grief, betrayal, torture, and death himself. So whatever you're facing, you're not facing it watched by a stranger. 'The Lord is close to the brokenhearted' — Psalm 34:18. If you're in a dark place right now, that's exactly where this God has promised to meet people. You're not alone. He came in.",
